default2.6 The challenges that isolated communities face as a result are even greater, given the need for two and sometimes three flights to reach an internat
defaultional destination. Airlines like ourselves try to assist our passengers wherever possible by operating direct routes to 
defaultinternational hubs, such as Exeter to Paris CDG or Inverness to Amsterdam. This enables them to access global airports and negates the n
defaulteed for hours spent on the road driving to say London Heathrow or Birmingham. 
defaultMore direct routes could be introduced were the funding available.
default&#xa0;
default2.7 Another alternative Flybe has developed is the Manchester hub.
default Intro
defaultduced in March 2012, we
default created a regi
defaultonal network hub by optimising scheduling options through Manchester airport, meaning that Flybe passengers instantly benefitted from an additional 86 regional point-to-point connections.
default 
defaultBy working with Manchester Airport to streamline connectivity and re
defaultduce minimum connecting times to as little as 35 minutes, Flybe significantly added to the choice of our domestic flights, giving passengers an affordable choice of multiple day returns throughout the UK. While the hub can never be, and does not seek to be
default, a rival to Heathrow, it has created a long-haul alternative to for the UK’s regional communities, allowing them to access flight connections to the rest of the world offered from Manchester Airport.
