default&#xa0;default3.1 
defaultAir Passenger Duty is a barrier to economic growth. It is well documented that the UK has the highest aviation tax in the world – a seriously short-sighted policy for an island nation. Indeed, the government themselves have explicitly acknowledged that APD
default constrains demand, evidenced by their decision 
defaultin 2011 
defaultto approve a reduction in Continental’s APD from Belfast International to Newark in order to retain the service.
